article.description:
Shannon Johnson scored 25 points, including six in Orlando's deciding 10-0 run, and the Miracle won for the first
time ever at Madison Square Garden with a 71-62 victory over the New York Liberty on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Miracle win for first time at MSG
article.linkText: Garden Miracle: Orlando finally wins at MSG
article.story:
NEW YORK (AP) -- Shannon Johnson scored 25 points, including six
in Orlando's deciding 10-0 run, and the Miracle won for the first
time ever at Madison Square Garden with a 71-62 victory over the
New York Liberty on Tuesday night.

	   Nykesha Sales added 15 points for the Miracle (4-3), who had
lost their first five games in New York. Taj McWilliams-Franklin
had 10 points for Orlando, which had lost its last two games and
were playing the first game in a stretch that will have the Miracle
on the road for six of seven.

	   "When we came into the building I reminded them this team had
never won here and we have to play aggressive on the road we did
that from the start and took the crowd out of the game early,''
said first-year Miracle coach Dee Brown, who played in the NBA.

	   Johnson, a point guard who also had eight rebounds and four
assists, called winning in the Garden "the best thing that's
happened to us so far.''

	   Orlando got some in-person support from someone who won a lot of
games in Madison Square Garden, former Knicks center Patrick Ewing
who now plays for Orlando and was a teammate of Brown's with the
Magic.

	   "He really supports us and Dee,'' Johnson said.

	   Crystal Robinson had 19 points for the Liberty (7-4), who were
unbeaten in three home games this season and had won three of four
overall. Becky Hammon added 15 points for New York, while Tari
Phillips had 14 and Tamika Whitmore 11.

	   Teresa Weatherspoon's jumper with 6:25 to go gave New York a
57-55 lead. Orlando then went on the 10-0 run that was capped by
two free throws by Sales with 47 seconds to go.

	   Robinson made two of three free throws to get New York within
65-59, but that was as close as the Liberty would get.

	   "She's playing as well as anyone in the league,'' Liberty coach
Richie Adubato said of Johnson, who was 7-of-15 from the field and
10-of-14 from the free throw line. "We wasted good efforts by
Crystal and Becky. We got outrebounded (31-24) and we also had 17
turnovers and they got 21 points from them. That's not our game.''

	   The Miracle, who led 33-31 at halftime, led by as many as 10
points in the first half, 15-5.

	   New York is now 8-3 all-time against Orlando.
